    "objects": {
      "general": [
        {
          "properties": {
            "paragraphs": [
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Introduction",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "SHV follows the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) standards from",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "the US Department of Labor for incident reporting. These renowned standards are",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "also used by other corporates and align with reporting under CSRD. The",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "definitions of the main OSHA terms used in this report are outlined below: ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Total Recordable Case Frequency (TRCF)",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Ratio of number of recordable injuries per 100 employees per year, based on the",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "number of recordable injuries and worked hours. TRCF excludes contractors",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "working under supervision (CSRD definition: non-employees) in",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "this report.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Recordable injuries",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "An injury is a ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "recordable ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontStyle": "italic",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "injury if an employee or contractor that works under supervision of SHV or the Groups is physically injured resulting from events or exposures in the work environment.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Recordable injuries can be classified into categories that define the employees’ ability to continue their regular work and concern: Fatality, Lost Time Incident, Restricted Work Case, Medical Treatment Case and Loss of Consciousness",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "*",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontWeight": "bold",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": ". Other cases, such as First Aid or Near Miss do not concern a ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "Recordable",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontStyle": "italic",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": " ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "Injuries",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontStyle": "italic",
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": " but ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  },
                  {
                    "value": "are nevertheless tracked by the Groups to prevent recurrence.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "The aforementioned injury categories usually correspond to severity levels, although this is not always the case. For example, oxygen deficiency in a hydrogen tank resulting in the loss of consciousness can be classified as a SIF.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "Therefore, besides the different categories indicating the employees’ ability to continue their work, the most serious injuries are classified as Severe Injury or Fatality (SIF). This enables management to explicitly follow-up on the most serious incidents.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": " ",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "In addition, potential SIFs (PSIFs) are tracked, which could have resulted in a SIF if the circumstances had been slightly different.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": ""
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
                  {
                    "value": "The definitions of injury categories and SIFs are outlined in the next paragraph.",
                    "textStyle": {
                      "fontSize": "8pt",
                      "color": "black"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "listType": "bullet"
              },
              {
                "textRuns": [
